children.text: There is a roof truss that has been split/damaged.
The truss manufacturer warns in their installation instructions that
‘Any damaged trusses should be reported immediately and not site repaired without approval of the truss fabricator’ .
Additionally, the relevant Australian Standard, AS 4440 Installation of Nail-Plated Timber Roof Trusses, clause 3.10 Rejection Criteria, states the following;

The builder should consult the roof truss manufacturer to provide documentation and/or a design for the rectification, or otherwise to confirm that the current installation is acceptable. The builder should provide a copy of the documentation from the manufacturer to the owner for their records.
